<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="smell-v">smell <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /smel/    美 /smel/  </p>
<p>(smelt / smelled, smelt / smelled)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>闻；嗅：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She bent down and smelt the flowers.
她弯下腰闻了闻花。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sharks can smell blood over a long distance.
鲨鱼很远就能闻到血腥味。</p><footer>译林③ – 1</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[不用于进行时] 闻到：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>smell sth doing:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I smell something burning in the kitchen.
我闻到厨房里有东西烧焦了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[用作系动词] 闻起来有...的气味 / 气息：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>smell + adj / prep:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The flowers smell sweet.
这些花闻起来很香。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My room smells like / of a cigarette smoke.
我的房间闻起来有烟味。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You smell wonderful — what perfume is that?
你闻起来真香——那是什么香水？</p></div>

<h4 id="4can-could">4.<strong>[常与can, could连用] 闻到气味；有嗅觉：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He can’t smell because he has a cold.
因为感冒，他闻不出味道。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>[不用于进行时] 有难闻的气味；有臭气：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Your feet smell!
你的脚好臭！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The fish smells; I don’t think it’s quite fresh.
这条鱼有臭味，我认为它不新鲜了。</p></div>

<h4 id="6">6.<strong>[不用于被动语态] 察觉出；感觉到：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I can smell a festival atmosphere.
我能感觉到节日的气氛。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I can <strong>smell trouble</strong>.
我感到有麻烦了。</p></div></div>